Git version control system:



It is used to store the history of code 


Repository: it is a container stored some data


Version control two types


1)Centralized  : it dosent contain own repository when system crash or user not conected he cant see history 


Of code and he cant acess code



2)Distributed  :  in distributed control system each user as 

Own repository


Ex:git



//Git commands


Git init: convert a directory into git local repository



Git config --global user.name : to connect git hub account to vscode 

Git config --global email  : to connect github to vs code editor



Git add :  to track the files we need take files into staging area     git add . is used to take all files into staging area


Git commit:It is used to record the changes in the local  repository Commit the code  Git commit -m " update data" : m - indicates message


Git log: Showing the log of data

Git status: to know current status of repository it show current branch if any change shows files in staging area is their is no change show nothing


Git checkout : Git checkout is used to move backward code by using unique id id is know by using git status also 


Git pull: To take centeral data to local and check all data is updated or not


Git push : To push the changes to central or main server



Git clone:  To clone a git repository by using git clone 


Git rm :  to remove a file


Git mv:  used to rename a file


Git branch:  to know currently in which branch


Create branch: git branch branchname


Git checkout: move to another branch


Git merge : is used to merge two projects  git merge branchname


git branch -d branchname : to remove a branch



connected to remot6e repository 


git remote add orgin "url"


git log --online: give history in online


git revert: is used to revert to previous changes


git stash: is used to save changes when not ready in commit




